-- 3i to Name Borrows as Chief Executive Officer, Sunday Times Says
-- B y   S i m o n   P a c k a r d
-- 2012-05-13T06:19:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-13/3i-to-name-borrows-as-chief-executive-officer-sunday-times-says.html
3I Group Plc (III)  will name Simon Borrows
as chief executive officer this week to replace Michael Queen,
the Sunday Times said, without saying where it obtained the
information.  Borrows, 53, joined the buyout company in October as chief
investment officer and replaces Queen, who resigned in March
under pressure from shareholders, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Simon Packard in London at 
 packard@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dick Schumacher in London at 
 dschumacher@bloomberg.net  